Sentencas: A novel Pr2NiO4 (PNO)-Pr0.2Ce0.8O1.9 (PCO) composite material was synthesized by typical solid state mixing and modified sol-gel method, and was assessed as a cathode material candidate for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells (IT-SOFCs).
Titulo: Pr2NiO4-Pr0.2Ce0.8O1.9 composite cathode as a potential cathode material for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The effects of different preparation methods on the microstructure, transport properties, and stability of electrode materials were systematically investigated.
Titulo: Pr2NiO4-Pr0.2Ce0.8O1.9 composite cathode as a potential cathode material for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: It was found that the introduction of PCO enhanced the electrochemical activity of PNO electrode.
Titulo: Pr2NiO4-Pr0.2Ce0.8O1.9 composite cathode as a potential cathode material for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Among the composite materials, PNO-PCO composite cathode obtained by sol-gel method exhibited the best electrochemical performance.
Titulo: Pr2NiO4-Pr0.2Ce0.8O1.9 composite cathode as a potential cathode material for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The polarization resistance (R-p) on GDC electrolyte was 0.09 Omega cm(2) at 800 degrees C.
Titulo: Pr2NiO4-Pr0.2Ce0.8O1.9 composite cathode as a potential cathode material for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The NiO-GDC/GDC/PNO-PCO single cell yielded maximum output power of 0.57 W cm(-2) at 800 degrees
Titulo: Pr2NiO4-Pr0.2Ce0.8O1.9 composite cathode as a potential cathode material for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: C. Furthermore, the R-p exhibited an excellent stability after polarization for 120 h, indicating the good chemical compatibility of PNO-PCO composite cathode with other cell components.
Titulo: Pr2NiO4-Pr0.2Ce0.8O1.9 composite cathode as a potential cathode material for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The desirable electrochemical properties and stability of PNO-PCO composite demonstrate its potential as a cathode material for IT-SOFCs.
Titulo: Pr2NiO4-Pr0.2Ce0.8O1.9 composite cathode as a potential cathode material for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells
